  "text": "The Kubernetes controller work queue with rate limiting is implemented in the client-go library, which is vendored in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository under staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/. The implementation consists of several core components:\n\n1. **Core Queue Interface** (queue.go): The TypedInterface[T comparable] defines the fundamental queue operations Add(item T), Get() (item T, shutdown bool), and Done(item T). The Typed[t comparable] struct implements this interface with thread-safe operations using sync.Cond. The underlying storage uses a Queue[T] interface with a slice-based FIFO implementation.\n\n2. **Rate Limiting Queue** (rate_limiting_queue.go): The TypedRateLimitingInterface[T comparable] extends TypedDelayingInterface[T] with rate limiting capabilities. It defines methods AddRateLimited(item T), Forget(item T), and NumRequeues(item T). The rateLimitingType[T] struct wraps the delaying interface with a TypedRateLimiter[T] to implement these features.\n\n3. **Rate Limiters** (default_rate_limiters.go): Multiple rate limiter implementations are provided:\n   - TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter[T]: Implements exponential backoff with baseDelay*2^<num-failures>, capped at maxDelay. Tracks per-item failure counts in a map protected by mutex.\n   - TypedBucketRateLimiter[T]: Wraps golang.org/x/time/rate.Limiter for token bucket rate limiting with 10 qps and 100 burst size by default.\n   - TypedMaxOfRateLimiter[T]: Combines multiple limiters and returns the worst-case (maximum) delay.\n   - TypedItemFastSlowRateLimiter[T]: Provides fast retry for initial attempts, then slower retry after maxFastAttempts.\n   - TypedWithMaxWaitRateLimiter[T]: Wraps another limiter and caps the maximum wait time.\n\n4. **DefaultTypedControllerRateLimiter[T]()** (default_rate_limiters.go:48-56): The default rate limiter for controllers combines ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter (5ms base, 1000s max) with BucketRateLimiter (10 qps, 100 burst) using MaxOfRateLimiter to apply both per-item and overall rate limiting.\n\n5. **Delaying Queue** (delaying_queue.go): Provides AddAfter(item T, duration) capability, used by the rate limiting queue to delay items based on the rate limiter's decision.\n\n6. **Example Controller Pattern** (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/examples/workqueue/main.go): Demonstrates the standard controller reconciliation pattern:\n   - Uses informers to watch resources and add them to the queue via Add()\n   - Worker goroutines call Get() to retrieve items\n   - Defer Done(item) to mark processing as complete\n   - On error, call AddRateLimited(key) to requeue with backoff\n   - Call Forget(key) on success to reset the failure count\n   - This pattern is implemented throughout Kubernetes controllers\n\n7. **Real Controller Implementations**: Multiple controllers in pkg/controller/ use TypedRateLimitingInterface[string], including:\n   - TokenCleaner and BootstrapSigner: Manage bootstrap tokens and certificates\n   - CertificateController: Handles CSR approval/denial\n   - DaemonController, DeploymentController, JobController, StatefulSetController: Core workload controllers\n   - EndpointSliceController, EndpointSliceMirroringController: Network endpoint management\n   - NamespaceController, GarbageCollector, NodeLifecycleController: Cluster maintenance\n   - ResourceQuotaController, DisruptionController: Resource and policy enforcement\n   - ClusterRoleAggregationController: RBAC aggregation\n   Each follows the reconcile pattern: Get() → sync business logic → AddRateLimited() on error → Forget() on success → Done().\n\nThe rate limiting queue is initialized in each controller using NewTypedRateLimitingQueueWithConfig() with DefaultTypedControllerRateLimiter[T]() to provide both per-item exponential backoff and overall token bucket limiting."
}

